fields.Title: WHIRLING F1 / THE GARDENER MAIN
fields.Description: The Gardener turns out to be a Union fixer. Slightly different model and portrait. Short *smug* dialogue directing you to Hardie, referencing last dialogue.

fields.Title: You: "What if I want to, it's in my mind..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What if I want to, it's in my mind for some reason...

fields.Title: Jump to: [Elizabeth: ""That's Titus. Talk to him. But kno..."]
Elizabeth: ""Of course, and I'm just an epiderm..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course, and I'm just an epidermochromatic counsellor for the Dockworkers' Union," she says without blinking an eye.

fields.Title: You: ""He said Mr. Evrart sent you to law..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He said Mr. Evrart sent you to law school?"

fields.Title: You: ""He said you're Mr. Evrart's *Doux..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He said you're Mr. Evrart's *Doux et Sucré* Death Machine."

fields.Title: Authority: "How is that sign cleanup going, huh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: How is that sign cleanup going, huh? Fuck the police and all that? She said she would clean it.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""*Just dock workers*? Do dock worke..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Just dock workers*? Do dock workers spy on the Police? We let you off easy, miss. Don't think it will happen again."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Don't thank her -- thank me.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't thank her -- thank me."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""No, Glen -- they aren't." Her tone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, Glen -- they aren't." Her tone is cold and uninvolved.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Detective Disorientated." She smil..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Detective Disorientated." She smiles coldly. "Are you still wondering where you are? This is Martinaise, in case you've forgotten. I advise you not to overstay your welcome."

fields.Title: You: ""Wait, and you are...?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wait, and you are...?"

fields.Title: You: ""What are you going to *do* to me?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you going to *do* to me?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Hmh..." The lieutenant is not sati..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmh..." The lieutenant is not satisfied with the approach.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""I suggest not wasting time on triv..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I suggest not wasting time on trivial pleasantries and focusing on why you are actually here -- Titus Hardie," she points to the tall man by the table.

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "A cheap deflection, but brutal. Thi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A cheap deflection, but brutal. This did not have the effect you desired, but it did *something*.

fields.Title: You: ""Hold on, of course I *get it*. It'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hold on, of course I *get it*. It's a progressive soundscape, mixing nomadic rhythms with pop melodies."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Get sober." Her expression stiffen..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Get sober." Her expression stiffens. "Do your *job*. Ask your questions and get the hell out of Martinaise."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Listen, you Moralintern lackeys. Y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Listen, you Moralintern lackeys. You're a mob, enforcing the unlawful privatization of Revachol. Twenty fat men in the Occident are stealing it all -- and you're their body guards."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "She means it's part of the future y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She means it's part of the future you won't experience.

fields.Title: You: ""I was just making an observation...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I was just making an observation. I was reacting to stimuli."

fields.Title: You: ""I just wanted to know more about t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I just wanted to know more about the place before I check it out. That's normal."

fields.Title: You: ""The world needs a financial buffer..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The world needs a financial buffer zone. No need to get emotional."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, let's change the topic.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, let's change the topic."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""You should.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You should."

fields.Title: Authority: "*Why* did you say that? Did you for..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Why* did you say that? Did you forget you're a cop... again?

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, stick with your opinion.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, stick with your opinion."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "She's right, you're basically an ep..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She's right, you're basically an epidermochromatic police officer.

fields.Title: You: ""You're the gardener!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're the gardener!"

fields.Title: Authority: "You set the pace and the topic of t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You set the pace and the topic of these conversations here. Establish that.

fields.Title: Drama: "A man like Easy Leo could have said..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A man like Easy Leo could have said anything. Do not be restrained, sire.

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Hjelmdallermen is a reference to th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Hjelmdallermen is a reference to the *Northern* themed action-adventure series, Man From... Actually, this is less than helpful right now. I'll just get out of the way.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Let's." Her expression stiffens."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's." Her expression stiffens.

fields.Title: Authority: "I saw what you were thinking. You w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I saw what you were thinking. You want to say 'what are you going to *do* to me?'. Don't. Just because it's in your head doesn't mean you have to say it.

fields.Title: You: ""Are you Lizzy -- Elizabeth -- Miss..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you Lizzy -- Elizabeth -- Miss Beaufort?"

fields.Title: You: ""Why are you so aggressive?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why are you so aggressive?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You seem a little different today...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You seem a little different today. Less hospitable."

fields.Title: Glen: ""So fucking what? Lots of models ar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So fucking what? Lots of models are actually really smart people, fuckwad!"

fields.Title: You: ""Oh, you're a hjelmdaller-head?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh, you're a hjelmdaller-head?"

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""If anything, it is the RCM who *do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If anything, it is the RCM who *do* things to people..." She shakes her head. "But we digress."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Hmh. So you were spying on us. And..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmh. So you were spying on us. And now you represent murder suspects -- *just dock workers*."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""I'm being aggressive?" She raises..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm being aggressive?" She raises her eyebrows. "Listen, you Moralintern lackey, you're part of a mob, enforcing the unlawful privatization of Revachol. Twenty fat men in the Occident are stealing it all -- and you are their body guard."

fields.Title: You: ""This is not winner attitude, citiz..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is not winner attitude, citizen." (Shake your head.)

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Fine." She hands you her pair of y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fine." She hands you her pair of yellow gardening gloves.

fields.Title: You: ""Thank you comrade. Property is the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you comrade. Property is theft."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""You're right. I shouldn't have.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right. I shouldn't have."

fields.Title: Drama: "Her entire character has shifted. T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Her entire character has shifted. This young woman is cold as ice.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Officer Discotheque." She smiles c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Officer Discotheque." She smiles coldly. "Still wondering if we listen to disco? We don't, by the way. We don't listen to disco anymore."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Let me handle this," the woman say..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let me handle this," the woman says to the crowd in the mess hall before turning to you...

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""The Union isn't going to *do* anyt..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The Union isn't going to *do* anything to you. It is not a crime syndicate, it is a labour organization."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""I don't need privatization paeans..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't need privatization paeans from a rent-a-cop." Her expression stiffens. "Just do your *job*. Ask your questions. Then get out of Martinaise."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""You're far from home, *lieutenants..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're far from home, *lieutenants*... This isn't a district known for its love of self-proclaimed militiamen."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Sure, you were *curious*... I'm no..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure, you were *curious*... I'm not a gardener, by the way, I'm a legal counsellor for the Dockworkers' Union." She crosses her arms.

fields.Title: You: ""He said you were in debt to Mr. Cl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He said you were in debt to Mr. Claire."

fields.Title: Volition: "You will not lose out on anything g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You will not lose out on anything good by not saying it.

fields.Title: You: ""I guess you're not a winner after..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I guess you're not a winner after all."

fields.Title: Glen: ""You *could* be, Liz. You could be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You *could* be, Liz. You could be anything. You could even be a model."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Okay, you have a dictionary. That..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, you have a dictionary. That doesn't mean you get it..."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: "She doesn't say anything."
fields.Dialogue Text: She doesn't say anything.

fields.Title: You: ""I didn't deserve this handout. You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I didn't deserve this handout. You should've forced me to *hustle* harder."

fields.Title: You: ""I mean no trouble, I'm here to do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I mean no trouble, I'm here to do my job, that's all."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""You are looking for Titus Hardie,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You are looking for Titus Hardie, who you think has information on a murder the RCM is investigating. You want to interview him." She points to the man standing in the middle of the room.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Hjelmdallermen.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hjelmdallermen."

fields.Title: You: ""That's right, this is an epidermoc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's right, this is an epidermochromatic police officer. Deal with it."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Yes, extremely normal... I'm not a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, extremely normal... I'm not a gardener, by the way, I'm a legal counsellor for the Dockworkers' Union." She crosses her arms.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: "She says nothing; her glare speaks..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She says nothing; her glare speaks for her.

fields.Title: You: ""Get a grip Glen. She went to law s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Get a grip Glen. She went to law school."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""He said no such thing." She accide..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He said no such thing." She accidentally raises her voice. "This isn't about me."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Do dock workers spy on the Police?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do dock workers spy on the Police? You were on that corner all day. Now we know why." He smiles: "Just dock workers..."

fields.Title: You: ""The privatization is not unlawful,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The privatization is not unlawful, it's *cool* and *funny*. Maybe you're just not historic individuals?"

fields.Title: You: ""He's right, you know? You're very..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He's right, you know? You're very pretty."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""No.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No."

fields.Title: You: ""Thank you.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Thank you."

fields.Title: You: ""Be straight with me, what kind of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Be straight with me, what kind of music *do* you listen to?"

fields.Title: You: ""Dance music -- basically disco? I..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Dance music -- basically disco? I know all about it."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""You're far from home, *officer*......"
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're far from home, *officer*... This isn't a district known for its love of self-proclaimed militiamen."

fields.Title: You: ""I mean no trouble, just here to do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I mean no trouble, just here to do my job, that's all."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""I've got nothing to say to you. Wh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I've got nothing to say to you. Why are you wasting your time?" She crosses her arms.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""I represent the Union and these me..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I represent the Union and these men here." She points to the crew around the table. "Don't make this personal."

fields.Title: Authority: "You were specifically asked *not* t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You were specifically asked *not* to say that -- and then you said it anyway. You junior delinquent! But you *still* did!

fields.Title: You: ""I don't know where you heard that,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I don't know where you heard that, but it's wrong. The RCM is principled and *strong*, unlike you socialists."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Look -- a comedian." Her expressio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look -- a comedian." Her expression stiffens. "Do your *job*. Ask your questions. Then get out of Martinaise."

fields.Title: You: ""I have a cadaver situation. I woul..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I have a cadaver situation. I would really appreciate it."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""You're far from home, *lieutenants..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're far from home, *lieutenants*... This isn't a district known for its love of self-proclaimed militiamen."

fields.Title: Drama: "Her entire character has shifted. T..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Her entire character has shifted. This young woman is cold as ice.

fields.Title: You: ""You're right, lieutenant, she did..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right, lieutenant, she did seem friendlier sitting on that corner."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay, let's put on a new record."..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, let's put on a new record." (Conclude.)

fields.Title: You: ""I just wanted to know what kind of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I just wanted to know what kind of music you listen to. I was just curious!"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It doesn't matter if you recognize..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It doesn't matter if you recognize our authority. We will make an arrest if we have to."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Mhm..." A gruff humph from the tab..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Mhm..." A gruff humph from the table. "Goddamn right it is."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""*Even* a mod..." Her face stiffens..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "*Even* a mod..." Her face stiffens. "Glen, I went to *law school*. I am an attorney."

fields.Title: Authority: "She shut you down -- because you do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She shut you down -- because you don't have enough backbone.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "A left jab, right in the looker."
fields.Dialogue Text: A left jab, right in the looker.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""I guess it's fair to say you guys..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I guess it's fair to say you guys have it on life support."

fields.Title: You: ""Enough. Let's talk seriously.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Enough. Let's talk seriously."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""What you want is of no significanc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What you want is of no significance, *officer*. Don't test your authority -- in Martinaise you are no one."

fields.Title: You: ""He said you're the Union fixer. Yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He said you're the Union fixer. You fix things."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Detective Skin-Colour." She smiles..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Detective Skin-Colour." She smiles coldly. "I'm still black as you can see. Do you have any more keen-eyed observations?"

fields.Title: Elizabeth: "Not a muscle moves in her face, but..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not a muscle moves in her face, but her eyes trace yours, stern and perceptive.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""It's beyond the horizon for you.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's beyond the horizon for you."

fields.Title: You: ""The hell it is.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "The hell it is."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Look, we're not discussing your ta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look, we're not discussing your taste in music anymore, officer. Do you have questions for my clients or not?"

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""I. Don't. Care.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I. Don't. Care."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "There is nothing a determined man c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is nothing a determined man could not achieve.

fields.Title: You: ""You're not a gardener!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're not a gardener!"
fields.Alternate1: "I knew you were not the gardener!"

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Dirty tactics, officer."
fields.Dialogue Text: Dirty tactics, officer.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Fuck yeah," the tall, broad should..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fuck yeah," the tall, broad shouldered man takes a sip of his beer.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: "She shrugs. Almost no reaction."
fields.Dialogue Text: She shrugs. Almost no reaction.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Another day -- hustlin' and grindin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Another day -- hustlin' and grindin' in the free world!

fields.Title: You: ""You're right. I don't know anythin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right. I don't know anything about anything. What is anodic music?"

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Let's.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's."

fields.Title: You: ""You know, maybe you're right.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You know, maybe you're right."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""I will." It doesn't look like you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I will." It doesn't look like you changed her mind.

fields.Title: You: "Yeah, I don't care about that."
fields.Dialogue Text: Yeah, I don't care about that.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""So ask what you came to ask -- or..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "So ask what you came to ask -- or get back to your commanders."

fields.Title: You: ""The obscene sign. You said you wou..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The obscene sign. You said you would clean it.

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""C'mon Lizzie." The big man takes a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "C'mon Lizzie." The big man takes a sip of beer. "We're generous people here in Martinaise. With *property*."

fields.Title: You: ""What if I want to talk to *you*, n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What if I want to talk to *you*, not Titus?"

fields.Title: Composure: "Even though she has excellent contr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Even though she has excellent control over her self, something moved behind her eyes, in the way she stands, in her face...

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""That's right, I'm not a gardener,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's right, I'm not a gardener, I'm a legal counsellor for the Dockworkers' Union." She crosses her arms.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Of course, you were just doing you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Of course, you were just doing your *job*... I'm not a gardener, by the way, I'm a legal counsellor for the Dockworkers' Union." She crosses her arms.

fields.Title: You: ""Hardie? Not yet, I had another que..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hardie? Not yet, I had another question."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Not only do you *get it* -- you kno..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Not only do you *get it* -- you know it.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: "The cold look in her eyes speaks lo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The cold look in her eyes speaks louder than words: she is not amused.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Anodic dance music, you wouldn't g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Anodic dance music, you wouldn't get it."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Your understanding of the worker's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your understanding of the worker's struggle is about one century old, she's thinking.

fields.Title: Empathy: "You will never be able to experienc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You will never be able to experience it the way she does. She's even a bit sad about it; then the feeling passes.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""You're far from home, *officer*......"
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're far from home, *officer*... This isn't a district known for its love of self-proclaimed militiamen."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""You're not here to chat up the leg..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're not here to chat up the legal counsel, you're here to question these men."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""I am a *legal counsel*," she inton..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I am a *legal counsel*," she intones. "Don't make this personal."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""I have heard about your *medical c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I have heard about your *medical condition*. People talk. And I have no patience for it. Or pity."

fields.Title: You: ""Okay.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay."

fields.Title: Logic: "Uhm...  you're sure Easy Leo mentio..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Uhm...  you're sure Easy Leo mentioned something about a lawyer Elizabeth someone... but you're too *dumb* to remember what it was.

fields.Title: Authority: "A very minor victory."
fields.Dialogue Text: A very minor victory.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Aggressive? You make your living e..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Aggressive? You make your living enforcing violence. These people are just *dock workers*."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Sure, why be interested in the worl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sure, why be interested in the world around us. Get back to boring, brutal detective work.

fields.Title: You: ""The sign is going to have to clean..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The sign is going to have to clean itself then?"

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Please do.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Please do."

fields.Title: You: ""Hey. Can I borrow your gardening g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey. Can I borrow your gardening gloves?"

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""My answer is no.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "My answer is no."

fields.Title: Titus Hardie: ""Don't thank her -- thank me.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't thank her -- thank me."

fields.Title: You: ""I should talk to Titus then!" [Lea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I should talk to Titus then!" [Leave.]

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""What are we going to *do* to you?"..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are we going to *do* to you?" She starts laughing. It's a cold laughter, devoid of joy.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: "She looks as if pondering whether t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She looks as if pondering whether to answer or not... but then shakes her head slightly.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Sure, reacting to stimuli... I'm n..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sure, reacting to stimuli... I'm not a gardener, by the way, I'm a legal counsellor for the Dockworkers' Union." She crosses her arms.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Like I already told you, I'm a leg..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Like I already told you, I'm a legal counsellor." She crosses her arms. "Do you have hearing problems?"

fields.Title: Logic: "Could this be the *Miss Beaufort* t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Could this be the *Miss Beaufort* that Easy Leo mentioned? The one Mr. Evrart sent to law school?

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""No. Talk to Titus.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. Talk to Titus."

fields.Title: You: ""I liked that. Good start. Let's ta..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I liked that. Good start. Let's take it a step further -- armed uprising. What are the Union's plans?"

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""This is about your alcoholism, isn..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is about your alcoholism, isn't it? People talk." She squints. "I have no patience for it. Or pity."

fields.Title: You: ""You shouldn't have assisted me lik..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You shouldn't have assisted me like that. I am your enemy. Nature is struggle."

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "This didn't change her opinion of y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This didn't change her opinion of you.

fields.Title: Authority: "You caught her off guard. Push her..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You caught her off guard. Push her some more.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""No," she steadies her breathing. "..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No," she steadies her breathing. "Not disco. Disco is *undead*."

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""No, I'm not a gardener, I'm a lega..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, I'm not a gardener, I'm a legal counsellor for the Dockworkers' Union." She crosses her arms.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""That's right, I'm not a gardener,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's right, I'm not a gardener, I'm a legal counsellor for the Dockworkers' Union." It feels like she's waiting for a reaction of some sort.

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Oh yeah, you *get it*."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh yeah, you *get it*.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""No." It doesn't look like she's in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No." It doesn't look like she's into popular adventure-fantasy.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""No one is emotional here." Her exp..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No one is emotional here." Her expression stiffens further. "Do your *job*. Ask your questions -- then leave."

fields.Title: Drama: "Strange. It's as if people don't be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Strange. It's as if people don't believe a cop could be a socialist revolutionary.

fields.Title: You: ""You lied to me! You're *not* a gar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You lied to me! You're *not* a gardener!"
fields.Alternate1: "I knew you were not a gardener!"

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Obviously I'm a lawyer. A legal co..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Obviously I'm a lawyer. A legal counsellor for the Dockworkers' Union." She crosses her arms. "I would urge you to consider what you say to my clients."

fields.Title: Encyclopedia: "Sorry."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sorry.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We've talked to Evrart Claire. We..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We've talked to Evrart Claire. We know who these men are. The Union's *militant* wing."

fields.Title: You: ""Are you the eighth Hardie boy -- A..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you the eighth Hardie boy -- A Hardie girl?"

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""I am not," she says dryly."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I am not," she says dryly.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Wow -- really? A political moment?..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wow -- really? A political moment? Now?

fields.Title: Shanky: ""Yeah, don't you forget -- T did yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah, don't you forget -- T did you a favour, popo."

fields.Title: Drama: "It's not her. She's not a Hardie gi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's not her. She's not a Hardie girl. Definitely.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""I'm a legal counsellor for the Doc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm a legal counsellor for the Dockworkers' Union. I've been watching you." It feels like she's waiting for a reaction of some sort.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""That's Titus. Talk to him. But kno..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's Titus. Talk to him. But know this: I'll be keeping an eye on you. No strong-arming, nothing official. The district of Martinaise does not recognize your authority to make arrests."

fields.Title: You: ""What do you mean *us guys*?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What do you mean *us guys*?"

fields.Title: You: ""Easy Leo told me about you, he lik..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Easy Leo told me about you, he likes to talk a lot."

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "He's right, with a face like that s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He's right, with a face like that she could be on the cover of La Débutante International.

fields.Title: Elizabeth: ""Vulgar idiot," she shakes her head..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Vulgar idiot," she shakes her head.
